00:27:48.100 --> 00:27:52.390
how are they preventing
against predatory lending?

00:27:52.390 --> 00:27:55.850
Because just through reading
some of the articles,

00:27:55.850 --> 00:28:00.850
it seems like that becomes a
gray line when you're targeting

00:28:00.850 --> 00:28:04.270
specific type of
customer who doesn't

00:28:04.270 --> 00:28:07.427
qualify for traditional loans.

00:28:07.427 --> 00:28:09.760
GARY GENSLER: So you're talking
about more broadly, just

00:28:09.760 --> 00:28:13.750
in terms of, how do we
guard in any country

00:28:13.750 --> 00:28:15.090
against predatory lending?

00:28:15.090 --> 00:28:16.850
It's hard.

00:28:16.850 --> 00:28:17.650
It's hard.

00:28:17.650 --> 00:28:23.140
The entire credit space
has a lot of protections

00:28:23.140 --> 00:28:26.260
and regulations starting in--

00:28:26.260 --> 00:28:30.220
well, I would say starting
hundreds of years ago, really.

00:28:30.220 --> 00:28:32.590
One would even go back
to the Hammurabi Code

00:28:32.590 --> 00:28:34.950
and say there was regulation
of interest rates.

00:28:34.950 --> 00:28:38.350
But in the modern
days, we embedded--

00:28:38.350 --> 00:28:40.840
let's take the US for a moment.

00:28:40.840 --> 00:28:42.570
Two really important things.

00:28:42.570 --> 00:28:45.010
One was the Equal
Credit Opportunity

00:28:45.010 --> 00:28:48.550
Act or what some
people call ECOA,

00:28:48.550 --> 00:28:51.347
which was in the
late 1960s and then

00:28:51.347 --> 00:28:53.680
something called the Fair
Credit Reporting Act, I think,

00:28:53.680 --> 00:28:54.880
by 1972.

00:28:54.880 --> 00:29:00.490
These two came out of an earlier
way, the fintech, an earlier

00:29:00.490 --> 00:29:05.950
wave of credit cards, an
earlier wave of lending

00:29:05.950 --> 00:29:10.818
and directly to this question
about whether it was fair

00:29:10.818 --> 00:29:11.860
and whether it was equal.

00:29:11.860 --> 00:29:15.790
Everybody had the same access,
Equal Credit Opportunity Act,

00:29:15.790 --> 00:29:18.790
that you couldn't differentiate
because of gender, or race,

00:29:18.790 --> 00:29:23.800
or nationality, and the like
and Fair Credit Reporting,

00:29:23.800 --> 00:29:25.470
that those credit reports.

00:29:25.470 --> 00:29:31.270
The things that we came to know
and in about 30 countries rely

00:29:31.270 --> 00:29:35.440
on, is these FICO scores from
a company called the Fair Isaac

00:29:35.440 --> 00:29:38.170
company, that those scores--

00:29:38.170 --> 00:29:40.710
we'd have to be able to
know something about them.

00:29:40.710 --> 00:29:43.120
And if we were
turned down, somebody

00:29:43.120 --> 00:29:47.980
has to explain to us
how we were turned down.

00:29:47.980 --> 00:29:50.950
Well, now, fast forward to 2020.

00:29:50.950 --> 00:29:51.790
Absolutely.

00:29:51.790 --> 00:29:52.840
The question is right.

00:29:52.840 --> 00:29:56.770
How can we protect that
we still have equal credit

00:29:56.770 --> 00:29:59.110
and that it's explainable?

00:29:59.110 --> 00:30:00.980
And why is somebody turned down?

00:30:00.980 --> 00:30:06.310
And once somebody is not
allowed to take credit,

00:30:06.310 --> 00:30:09.400
it gets tougher with artificial
intelligence and machine

00:30:09.400 --> 00:30:09.980
learning.

00:30:09.980 --> 00:30:11.530
It also gets tougher
when there's not

00:30:11.530 --> 00:30:13.510
a physical location.

00:30:13.510 --> 00:30:15.550
And thirdly, many
of these companies

00:30:15.550 --> 00:30:19.030
are not regulated or
registered as banks.

00:30:19.030 --> 00:30:21.760
And regulators around
the globe tended

00:30:21.760 --> 00:30:27.670
to look to banks to make
sure that these laws were

00:30:27.670 --> 00:30:28.780
fairly applied.

00:30:28.780 --> 00:30:31.850
Now, they also look to the
credit reporting agencies.

00:30:31.850 --> 00:30:35.740
So I think the real answer
is in these changing times,

00:30:35.740 --> 00:30:38.860
the official sector
around the globe

00:30:38.860 --> 00:30:43.570
has to adapt and sometimes
change a little bit of who

00:30:43.570 --> 00:30:47.110
is regulated and even if you're
a non-bank, that you still

00:30:47.110 --> 00:30:50.417
have to comply with some of
these things, importantly.

