GARY GENSLER: Let me just pause.

00:54:38.920 --> 00:54:42.270
They either have to partner
with a bank, which is the issuer

00:54:42.270 --> 00:54:43.680
bank partner model.

00:54:43.680 --> 00:54:46.380
And we're going to get to
LendingClub, I promise,

00:54:46.380 --> 00:54:50.220
that has that issuer partner,
that bank that's a partner.

00:54:50.220 --> 00:54:54.210
Or they tap into the
securitization markets.

00:54:54.210 --> 00:54:56.760
And so for those who
are not familiar,

00:54:56.760 --> 00:54:58.920
asset securitization
is the concept

00:54:58.920 --> 00:55:04.130
that the securities markets
are the investors in the loans,

00:55:04.130 --> 00:55:06.590
rather than holding
it on a bank's balance

00:55:06.590 --> 00:55:09.560
sheet or a finance
company's balance sheet.

00:55:09.560 --> 00:55:12.980
And that innovation, asset
securitization starting

00:55:12.980 --> 00:55:17.480
in the mortgage markets
40-plus years ago moved

00:55:17.480 --> 00:55:24.470
to the credit card markets
in a robust way by the 1990s,

00:55:24.470 --> 00:55:29.000
is a very real way
to lay off that side,

00:55:29.000 --> 00:55:32.000
meaning find somebody
else to be the investors,

00:55:32.000 --> 00:55:33.390
rather than have
a balance sheet.

00:55:33.390 --> 00:55:34.700
So back to you, Alexandro.

00:55:34.700 --> 00:55:39.010
It's either a partner bank
or asset securitization.

00:55:39.010 --> 00:55:41.620
AUDIENCE: So in the
end, these guys,

00:55:41.620 --> 00:55:46.750
these fintech companies are
second intermediary, right?

00:55:46.750 --> 00:55:49.810
