00:58:35.800 --> 00:58:38.710
is the personal loan business.

00:58:38.710 --> 00:58:42.730
Personal loans differ
from credit cards

00:58:42.730 --> 00:58:46.900
in an important way, is that
credit cards are what's known

00:58:46.900 --> 00:58:50.430
as a revolving line of credit.

00:58:50.430 --> 00:58:53.430
Each purchase adds to
your credit balance.

00:58:53.430 --> 00:58:54.870
You have a limit.

00:58:54.870 --> 00:58:58.980
If you're high, if you're super
prime or a prime borrower,

00:58:58.980 --> 00:59:00.030
your limit is higher.

00:59:00.030 --> 00:59:03.010
If you're sub-prime,
your limit is lower.

00:59:03.010 --> 00:59:07.500
That business of
revolving credit--

00:59:07.500 --> 00:59:10.200
about a trillion
dollars in the US.

00:59:10.200 --> 00:59:12.270
We now have this
personal loan business.

00:59:12.270 --> 00:59:15.540
It's only about one sixth
the size, about $160 billion

00:59:15.540 --> 00:59:17.340
in the US.

00:59:17.340 --> 00:59:19.620
That personal loan
business is generally

00:59:19.620 --> 00:59:23.670
term financing, a
specific term that you

00:59:23.670 --> 00:59:28.800
have to have an installment loan
and pay once every month for 36

00:59:28.800 --> 00:59:33.610
months or for 48 or 60 months.

00:59:33.610 --> 00:59:35.890
The underwriting
risk of a term loan

00:59:35.890 --> 00:59:39.490
is lower than the underwriting
risk of credit card

00:59:39.490 --> 00:59:42.520
business or revolving credit.

00:59:42.520 --> 00:59:46.210
The personal loan business is
where most of the disruptors

00:59:46.210 --> 00:59:47.180
are.

00:59:47.180 --> 00:59:51.820
The SoFis, and the Prospers,
and the Nubanks, and so forth--

00:59:51.820 --> 00:59:56.090
they're trying to break
in the personal loan

00:59:56.090 --> 01:00:02.015
side as much or even more
than the credit card side.

